beer.beer_description:
G'day mates,

Much like we did with Aussie Jingle Bells, we're taking something from our mates up north and making it our own.

Using a New England IPA base we've used an all Aussie hop line up to give you a flavour profile reminiscent of the topping on Mum's Christmas Day pavlova - fresh pineapples, mandarins and passionfruits.
beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy

items.badge_description: In our best David Attenborough impression Ah... and here we see the rare Leap Beer badge. More elusive than the rarest of beers, the Leap Beer badge emerges once every four years to share what liquid libations are being enjoyed by its numerous earners across the globe. The badge makes its appearance known widely across the community, but quickly returns to its long slumber, not set to emerge again for another four long years...

items.checkin_comment: I was a bit worried that this one would taste overly strong being a double, but it’s actually quite smooth and drinkable. They’ve done a good job of the flavour, I actually get stone fruit in this.

items.badge_description: Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!
We believe in IPA and you should too. You certainly have a taste for the hops! That's 255 different IPAs. Try 5 more for Level 52! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast
